##📈 Output
The Flask web app takes user input (N, P, K, temperature, humidity, pH, rainfall) and instantly returns the recommended crop. Multiple models were trained and compared; the best-performing one was saved as `best_model.pkl` and deployed in the app, giving accurate, real-time predictions through a clean web interface.

---

##✅ Final Conclusion
OptiCrop successfully shows how machine learning can support smarter farming by turning soil and environmental data into a clear, actionable crop recommendation. Through combined teamwork across data analysis, model building, backend, and frontend, the project delivers a complete working system that helps farmers pick the right crop, use resources more efficiently, and reduce the risk of crop failure — a practical step toward sustainable, data-driven agriculture.
